"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-katie-ledecky-is-chasing-her-own-greatness-paris-games-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t stop, won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t stop.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 41, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you want to distill 12 years of unparalleled greatness to its essence, that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s it.\", \"from\": 42, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even at the advanced swimming age of 27, she always wants to train, always wants to keep pushing, always is ready to grab the cap and goggles and do it again.\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even a single week off, after an unbroken year of some of the hardest aerobic work possible, made her uncomfortable.\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It certainly wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t voluntary when she did it last year, despite all she had accomplished.\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A lot of athletes say they have no \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009coff\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d switch; Ledecky legitimately lives that way.\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's even added a solo Sunday swim to her routine, making her a seven-day-a-week swimmer.\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is that commitment to the grind a sign of compulsion or devotion?\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps some of both.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s affection for swimming is real, as her new memoir makes clear.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a sport rife with burnout, she is the eternal flame.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED:Meet Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Roster for the 2024 Paris Olympics  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI can tell you, she wants to swim forever,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says her coach at Gator Swim Club, Anthony Nesty.\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 1065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1051, \"end\": 1064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Nesty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anthony Nesty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Nesty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Nesty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cBecause she enjoys it so much.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  She enjoys it enough to have built her entire lifestyle around it.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Early to bed, early to rise, a healthy eater, a non-partier, a limited romantic life, immune to social drama\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094all of it requires an unusual level of focus, but Ledecky has never seen that as a sacrifice.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s simply who she is and what it takes for her to do her best in what she loves most.\\u00c2  What she does is incredibly hard, but why she succeeds is also incredibly simple.\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1549, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She puts in the work, in every facet of her life.\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And she puts in the work because she loves it.\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheParis Olympicswill be Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fourth Summer Games.She wants to shoot for a fifth, on home soil (in home water?\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1765, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"), in Los Angeles four years from now.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1771, \"end\": 1782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.654743716084622e-29, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would equal Michael Phelps\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s five, and although she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll never match his 23 gold medals and 28 overall medals, she could do him one better by winning a medal in all five of her Olympics.\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Phelps did not win one at his first Summer Games in 2000.)\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7069982201013143e-16, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky has won gold as an anonymous teen in London, gold as an unbeatable giant in Rio de Janeiro and gold as a 24-year-old facing greater competition in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2104, \"end\": 2110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.036226628870922e-13, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2143, \"end\": 2157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.612993782900596e-28, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.997877701542266, \"rank\": 0.002126812186708858, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s won seven Olympic gold medals total\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and she will win more in Paris.\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2292, \"end\": 2297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.69911911555074e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the prohibitive favorite in the 1,500-meter freestyle and a solid favorite in the 800, not to mention a strong medal threat in the 400 and the 4X200 freestyle relay.\\u00c2  A host of new milestones for long-term excellence are within reach.\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two more golds would break American Jenny Thompson\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s record for the most by a female swimmer and tie the record for most by a female Olympian (Russian gymnast Larisa Latynina).\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2570, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999971691735532, \"rank\": 2.830356475869952e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2579, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Boyd\", \"score\": 0.9709684216305913, \"rank\": 0.025084642290254353, \"text\": \"Jenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Boyd\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Boyd\"}, {\"begin\": 2688, \"end\": 2695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"score\": 0.9668403300857557, \"rank\": 0.029688096248537837, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2704, \"end\": 2719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three more medals of any kind would give her 13, breaking the American female record of 12 held by Thompson and Dara Torres.\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2784, \"end\": 2792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999971691735532, \"rank\": 2.830356475869952e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2821, \"end\": 2829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9756186846446046, \"rank\": 0.024990619531382728, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 2834, \"end\": 2845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dara Torres\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a victory in the 800-meter freestyle, she can become the first woman to win four straight Olympic gold medals in the same event.\", \"from\": 2847, \"to\": 2980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So many big moments have already been achieved, with more to come.\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 3048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the smaller, daily moments that create her satisfaction.\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone who knows Ledecky will say she relishes practice more than the competitions.\", \"from\": 3122, \"to\": 3207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s despite the fact that swim practice is a grueling, largely solitary endeavor.\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Spending hours face-down, staring at a black line, communication coming only with gasping breaths between efforts\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not terribly social.\", \"from\": 3295, \"to\": 3438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not like a full-court scrimmage in basketball or seven-on-seven drills in football.\", \"from\": 3439, \"to\": 3530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It takes a different mindset to view those practices as not just survivable, but enjoyable.\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Megan Byrnes, who swam on the same club team with Ledecky in Washington, D.C., growing up and then with her in the distance group at Stanford, recalls doing weekly extra Tuesday workouts in college with members of the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094largely in order to give Ledecky tougher competition and additional yardage.\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3624, \"end\": 3629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Lloyd_George\", \"score\": 0.9230290765138355, \"rank\": 0.07985960670922265, \"text\": \"Megan\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Lloyd_George\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Lloyd_George\"}, {\"begin\": 3685, \"end\": 3695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"score\": 0.9997846048923865, \"rank\": 0.00021099927246834359, \"text\": \"Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Washington\"}, {\"begin\": 3685, \"end\": 3701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2568233962189774e-15, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}, {\"begin\": 3685, \"end\": 3701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2568233962189774e-15, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_metropolitan_area\"}, {\"begin\": 3757, \"end\": 3765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 0.9999998833900531, \"rank\": 1.1661023310028065e-07, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She said those workouts sometimes involved arduous 800-meter freestyle sets.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d say, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098This is going to be horrible,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Byrnes recalls.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd Katie would say, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098No, this is going to be fun.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 She will tackle the craziest sets and just go get it.\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s so mentally tough.\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t think there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s anybody that works as hard as she has for so long.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The extra workouts date back to before anyone knew who Ledecky was, prior to bursting on the scene by winning gold in London at age 15.\", \"from\": 4221, \"to\": 4437, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4420, \"end\": 4426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.036226628870922e-13, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She started doing a Sunday workout back then with coach Yuri Suguiyama, upping her weekly training distance to about 40 miles.\", \"from\": 4438, \"to\": 4564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pain was part of the package, but the pool was her happy place.\", \"from\": 4565, \"to\": 4628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From that point on, doing extra and finding faster (male) training partners became routine.\", \"from\": 4630, \"to\": 4721, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She chased Olympian Andrew Gemmell for thousands of meters in preparation for Rio in 2016, and in 2022 her move to Florida was largely based on the opportunity to throw down freestyle training sets with Olympians Bobby Finke and Kieran Smith.\\u00c2  On Friday afternoons in Gainesville, Fla., Finke and Ledecky often battle in brutally difficult workouts.\", \"from\": 4722, \"to\": 5072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4733, \"end\": 4741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.880960699466633e-21, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 4742, \"end\": 4756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Gemmell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Gemmell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Gemmell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Gemmell\"}, {\"begin\": 4800, \"end\": 4803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999993287929, \"rank\": 6.710014282843395e-10, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4837, \"end\": 4844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\", \"score\": 0.9999998972080046, \"rank\": 9.296515280345004e-08, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\"}, {\"begin\": 4935, \"end\": 4946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}, {\"begin\": 4951, \"end\": 4957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"score\": 0.9999999998981366, \"rank\": 1.0208418937098804e-10, \"text\": \"Kieran\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kieran_Culkin\"}, {\"begin\": 4991, \"end\": 5002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\", \"score\": 0.93643673275069, \"rank\": 0.05354165628922331, \"text\": \"Gainesville\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An example: three 2,000-meter swims in roughly an hour, with just a couple of minutes rest between them.\", \"from\": 5073, \"to\": 5177, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These are quite literally the premier distance workouts in the sport, a showdown between the two reigning Olympic champions in the 800 and 1,500-meter freestyles.\", \"from\": 5178, \"to\": 5340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And they are not a time or place for half-hearted effort.\", \"from\": 5341, \"to\": 5398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cKatie is a beast in practice,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Finke says.\", \"from\": 5400, \"to\": 5447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe have some Friday afternoon sets where she is just hammering away and I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m trying to chase her down, and it never works.\", \"from\": 5448, \"to\": 5574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been scary, amazing.\", \"from\": 5575, \"to\": 5602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a really big competitor and she doesn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t like losing, and I don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t like losing.\", \"from\": 5603, \"to\": 5692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIf I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m doing good, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s like, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098OK, how far ahead am I of Katie?\", \"from\": 5694, \"to\": 5766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She might catch me on the last one.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  RELATED:Who\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll Win in Paris?\", \"from\": 5767, \"to\": 5840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5834, \"end\": 5839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.69911911555074e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SI Picks Every Medal at the 2024 Olympics  Ledecky customarily downplays the days when she can beat Finke.\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5947, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cNinety-nine percent of the time Bobby is killing me,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 5948, \"to\": 6016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI find that one percent every now and then and have a good day where I can sneak ahead of him.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  The move to Florida was a business decision, one designed to keep her ahead of the world in the longest events and to help her catch up to the young guns who have swam faster in the 400\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Australia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Ariarne Titmus and Canada\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Summer McIntosh in recent yearshave swapped the world record that once belonged to Ledecky.\", \"from\": 6017, \"to\": 6442, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6131, \"end\": 6138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\", \"score\": 0.9999998972080046, \"rank\": 9.296515280345004e-08, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\"}, {\"begin\": 6321, \"end\": 6335, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 6351, \"end\": 6366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The presence of one of her old Stanford teammates, Nicole Stafford, in Gainesville helped ease the transition outside of the pool.\", \"from\": 6443, \"to\": 6573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6474, \"end\": 6482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 0.9999998833900531, \"rank\": 1.1661023310028065e-07, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}, {\"begin\": 6494, \"end\": 6509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Stafford\", \"score\": 0.9999939727176494, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicole Stafford\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Stafford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicole_Stafford\"}, {\"begin\": 6514, \"end\": 6525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\", \"score\": 0.93643673275069, \"rank\": 0.05354165628922331, \"text\": \"Gainesville\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gainesville,_Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stafford, who was working on her PhD in mechanical engineering at Florida, ate meals and watched sports with Ledecky.\", \"from\": 6575, \"to\": 6692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6575, \"end\": 6583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stafford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.439834956058188e-27, \"text\": \"Stafford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stafford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stafford\"}, {\"begin\": 6641, \"end\": 6648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\", \"score\": 0.9999998972080046, \"rank\": 9.296515280345004e-08, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s seen her former teammate grow from painful shyness to someone more comfortable in her internationally famous skin.\", \"from\": 6693, \"to\": 6815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve seen her open up a lot more,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Stafford says.\", \"from\": 6817, \"to\": 6873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6859, \"end\": 6867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stafford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.439834956058188e-27, \"text\": \"Stafford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stafford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stafford\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhen she came in at Stanford, sometimes talking to her felt like you were interviewing her.\", \"from\": 6874, \"to\": 6968, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6897, \"end\": 6905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 0.9999998833900531, \"rank\": 1.1661023310028065e-07, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the years, I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve seen her personality shine through.\", \"from\": 6969, \"to\": 7027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s put trust in people and she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sharing herself with people.\", \"from\": 7028, \"to\": 7096, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s actually pretty funny, and she cares a lot about people.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Case in point: When the two went out for brunch not long ago, Ledecky insisted on picking up the tab to celebrate Stafford\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s successful defense of her PhD thesis.\", \"from\": 7097, \"to\": 7330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Ledecky had just beenawarded the Presidential Medal of Freedom.\", \"from\": 7331, \"to\": 7405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky always has been genuinely happy for her teammates when they do well, at whatever level that might be.\", \"from\": 7407, \"to\": 7516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s chasing world records and gold medals, she can summon plenty of excitement for a friend who simply makes theU.S.\", \"from\": 7517, \"to\": 7643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"national teamor swims a personal-best time.\", \"from\": 7644, \"to\": 7687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A fan and student of the sport, she remembers what those achievements are like, and how much they meant to her on her journey to the top.\", \"from\": 7688, \"to\": 7825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s also easier for her to talk about everyone other than herself.\", \"from\": 7827, \"to\": 7896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI am perhaps naturally guarded,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she wrote in her pleasantly endearing and revealing memoir.\", \"from\": 7898, \"to\": 7995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cNot in a defensive way.\", \"from\": 7996, \"to\": 8022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More in an I-prefer-to-be-private sort of way.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  She let the guard down a little inJust Add Water, which can be considered a love letter to the sport that has made her a national hero.\", \"from\": 8023, \"to\": 8209, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The book is, like the author, bereft of controversy.\", \"from\": 8210, \"to\": 8262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is also, like the author, gracious to everyone who has helped her get to where she is.\", \"from\": 8263, \"to\": 8352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is rife with affectionate observations about family members, coaches and fellow swimmers.\", \"from\": 8353, \"to\": 8445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The recitation of her favorite pools around the world is like reading a famous chef\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s list of favorite restaurants.\", \"from\": 8447, \"to\": 8564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The chapters on her grandparents dive into the family history of unstinting effort and generosity.\", \"from\": 8565, \"to\": 8663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The chapters on her mom and dad reveal parents who encouraged their kids without excessive pushing.\", \"from\": 8664, \"to\": 8763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She describes them as \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cwhatever is the opposite of stage parents.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d (The chapter on her father, Dave, included the revelation that he still drives a 2008 Toyota Sienna, the CD player loaded with Bruce Springsteen discs.)\", \"from\": 8764, \"to\": 8987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8921, \"end\": 8934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Sienna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Toyota Sienna\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Sienna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Sienna\"}, {\"begin\": 8921, \"end\": 8934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Sienna\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Toyota Sienna\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Sienna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toyota_Sienna\"}, {\"begin\": 8962, \"end\": 8979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Springsteen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bruce Springsteen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Springsteen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Springsteen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the chapter on her older brother, Michael, with whom she is very close, has aRevenge of the Nerdsundertone to it.\", \"from\": 8989, \"to\": 9106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky reflects on each of them growing up without being \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthe coolest kid in our class.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d The energy Ledecky never expended on teenage drama and popularity was productively channeled into the pool.\", \"from\": 9107, \"to\": 9308, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cHe made me feel like it was O.K.\", \"from\": 9310, \"to\": 9345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9341, \"end\": 9345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OK\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2193022586884243e-38, \"text\": \"O.K.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OK\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/OK\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"to be a little different, or nerdy, or quirky,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Ledecky wrote.\", \"from\": 9346, \"to\": 9410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI found that perspective empowering in my own awkward girlhood years.\", \"from\": 9411, \"to\": 9483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I followed Michael\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s example and didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t spend much energy on what people thought of my wet hair and off-trend fashion choices as I juggled practices and school.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s had a different coach for each Olympic cycle and remains on great terms with all of them\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094which is not uniformly true in the sport.\", \"from\": 9484, \"to\": 9793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are a lot of bad breakups between swimmers and coaches, but none for Ledecky.\", \"from\": 9794, \"to\": 9877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She credits Suguiyama, her first national-level coach, with getting her to say out loud that she wanted to be an Olympian, and for developing her distinctive galloping freestyle stroke.\", \"from\": 9879, \"to\": 10064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9992, \"end\": 10000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.880960699466633e-21, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She salutes Bruce Gemmell at Nation\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Capital Aquatics withcharting the path to worldwide domination, highlighted by four gold medals in Rio.\", \"from\": 10065, \"to\": 10208, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10077, \"end\": 10090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Gemmell_(coach)\", \"score\": 0.9999865179733454, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bruce Gemmell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Gemmell_(coach)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bruce_Gemmell_(coach)\"}, {\"begin\": 10204, \"end\": 10207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999993287929, \"rank\": 6.710014282843395e-10, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She praises Greg Meehan at Stanford for helping guide her into adulthood and professional swimming (she set her most recent world record, in the 1,500 freestyle in 2018 during her first pro meet), and surviving the pandemic.\", \"from\": 10209, \"to\": 10433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10221, \"end\": 10232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Meehan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Greg Meehan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Meehan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greg_Meehan\"}, {\"begin\": 10236, \"end\": 10244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 0.9999998833900531, \"rank\": 1.1661023310028065e-07, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She appreciates that Nesty connected on a personal level and dared to fine-tune her stroke\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094which he described as \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cchoppy\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cinefficient\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094in an attempt to make the greatest distance swimmer better.\", \"from\": 10434, \"to\": 10645, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mostly, though, Ledecky writes bouquets to the sport itself.\", \"from\": 10647, \"to\": 10707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s impossible to do what she has done at the highest level for 12 years\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094to swim some of the hardest events, which require the most grueling practices\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094without deriving joy from it.\", \"from\": 10708, \"to\": 10895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cTo be doing it at this level for that long, it takes a special person,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Nesty says.\", \"from\": 10897, \"to\": 10985, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heading into Paris, she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the oldest female swimmer with a top-10 world time in 2024 in each of her three individual events\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the 400, 800 and 1,500.\", \"from\": 10987, \"to\": 11138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11000, \"end\": 11005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.69911911555074e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s seeded first in the 800 and 1,500, and second in the 400, ready to take on the young guns nipping at her heels.\", \"from\": 11139, \"to\": 11258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RELATED:Kate Douglass Is Set to Be Team USA\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Swiss-Army Knife in Paris  Swimming is a young person\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s game, especially on the female side.\", \"from\": 11260, \"to\": 11402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11268, \"end\": 11281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 11328, \"end\": 11333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.69911911555074e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 11335, \"end\": 11343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.823795253107422e-27, \"text\": \"Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Ledecky has evolved from phenom to terminator to elder stateswoman (and U.S. team captain) without losing much at all.\", \"from\": 11403, \"to\": 11525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s one of the few star swimmers who has never had an existential crisis that threatened to drive her from the sport.\", \"from\": 11526, \"to\": 11647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How many medals Ledecky wins in Paris, and what kind, is unknown as of now.\", \"from\": 11649, \"to\": 11724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11681, \"end\": 11686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.69911911555074e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only guarantees are these: She will try her hardest, and she will shed tears when it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s over.\", \"from\": 11725, \"to\": 11823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky cried at the end of her Rio Olympics.She cried at the end of her Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 11825, \"to\": 11913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She did the same after the2023 World Championships.\", \"from\": 11914, \"to\": 11965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s worth of work gets emptied into a pool at the end of a season, and then the emotions come forth.\", \"from\": 11966, \"to\": 12073, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI sometimes feel depleted after end-of-season meets,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Ledecky writes in her book.\", \"from\": 12075, \"to\": 12161, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI have so much tension built inside of me.\", \"from\": 12162, \"to\": 12207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When the meet ends, I take my first deep breath in months.\", \"from\": 12208, \"to\": 12266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s this emotional release after being laser-focused and locked down for such a long period of time.\", \"from\": 12267, \"to\": 12373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t control it.\", \"from\": 12374, \"to\": 12395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I deflate like a balloon.\", \"from\": 12396, \"to\": 12421, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I get in my feelings.\\\"\", \"from\": 12422, \"to\": 12444, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It cannot be easy chasing her own greatness, trying to replicate world records set years ago.\", \"from\": 12446, \"to\": 12539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s especially challenging when the rest of the world has gotten faster, trying to clear the bar Ledecky raised so high.\", \"from\": 12540, \"to\": 12663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But out of respect for swimming and love of the water, she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s still giving it everything she has, every single day.\", \"from\": 12664, \"to\": 12780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Without a doctor or coach\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s orders, Katie Ledecky can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t stop and won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t stop.\", \"from\": 12782, \"to\": 12864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12820, \"end\": 12833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Check out Sports Illustrated\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Daily Rings, our daily Olympics podcast from Mitch Goldich and Dan Gartland.\", \"from\": 12866, \"to\": 12975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 12944, \"end\": 12949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"score\": 0.9999998637395131, \"rank\": 1.3625889465725563e-07, \"text\": \"Mitch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hurricane_Mitch\"}, {\"begin\": 12966, \"end\": 12974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"score\": 0.9999999999708962, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gartland\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gartland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe wherever you get your podcasts (Apple,Spotify) and find clips onSI\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s YouTube page.\", \"from\": 12976, \"to\": 13070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13018, \"end\": 13023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.858581299861443e-14, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 13024, \"end\": 13031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spotify\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 13072, \"to\": 13098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Pat Forde is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated who covers college football and college basketball as well as the Olympics and horse racing.\", \"from\": 13099, \"to\": 13307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13163, \"end\": 13172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pat Forde\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pat_Forde\"}, {\"begin\": 13196, \"end\": 13214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.704269388763236e-55, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He cohosts the College Football Enquirer podcast and is a football analyst on the Big Ten Network.\", \"from\": 13308, \"to\": 13406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13390, \"end\": 13405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Big Ten Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Big_Ten_Network\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He previously worked for Yahoo Sports, ESPN and The (Louisville) Courier-Journal.\", \"from\": 13407, \"to\": 13488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13432, \"end\": 13444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\", \"score\": 0.815096196264302, \"rank\": 0.22684904844294426, \"text\": \"Yahoo Sports\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yahoo!_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 13446, \"end\": 13450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.311608844865652e-35, \"text\": \"ESPN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ESPN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forde has won 28 Associated Press Sports Editors writing contest awards, has been published three times in the Best American Sports Writing book series, and was nominated for the 1990 Pulitzer Prize.\", \"from\": 13489, \"to\": 13688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 13506, \"end\": 13522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.69602168425775e-15, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}, {\"begin\": 13600, \"end\": 13628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Best American Sports Writing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Best_American_Sports_Writing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A past president of the U.S. Basketball Writers Association and member of the Football Writers Association of America, he lives in Louisville with his wife.\", \"from\": 13689, \"to